song.name: Stumbled Beginnings…

scene_description: Nina stabs and kills Lily in the dressing room in between performances. She hides her body in the closet.
song.name: It's My Time
song.artist.name: Clint Mansell

scene_description: Song as Nina comes out to dance the Black Swan part of swan lake after killing Lily.
song.name: A Swan Is Born
song.artist.name: Clint Mansell

scene_description: After Nina realizes she stabbed herself. She goes on to dance her final part as the white swan. She jumps into the bed and says it was perfect.
song.name: Perfection
song.artist.name: Clint Mansell

scene_description: Played throughout the end credits.
song.name: A Swan Song (For Nina)
song.artist.name: Clint Mansell

scene_description: All credited songs contain samples of 'Swan Lake'
song.name: Swan Lake, Op.20: Scene
song.artist.name: Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky, London Symphony Orchestra & Pierre Monteux

scene_description: First song when Megamind realizes he was destined to be the bad guy. Continues as he escapes Prison.
song.name: Bad to the Bone

song.name: A Little Less Conversation - JXL Radio Edit Remix
song.artist.name: Elvis Presley & The Jordanaires

scene_description: After Megamind defeats and kills Metroman and they walk through the streets. Minion plays it on his stereo.
song.name: Highway To Hell

scene_description: Plays on Minion's stereo as he tries to stop 'Highway to Stop'
song.name: Lovin' You
song.artist.name: Minnie Riperton

scene_description: Megamind and Minion celebrate being the rulers of the Metrocity.
song.name: Crazy Train

song.name: Mr. Blue Sky

scene_description: Megamind searches the streets and waits to fight Titan.
song.name: Back in Black
song.artist.name: AC/DC

scene_description: During the final fight between Titan and Megamind. Megamind realizes that the hero he created is corrupt.
song.name: Welcome To The Jungle
song.artist.name: Guns N' Roses

scene_description: Megamind becomes the hero and his statue is revealed. He dances for the crowd to this song and it continues into the end credits.
song.name: Bad

song.name: Alone Again (Naturally)
song.artist.name: Gilbert O'Sullivan

scene_description: Opening titles. Hiccup introduces his island of Berk and tells about Vikings' confrontation with dragons
song.name: This Is Berk

scene_description: The tribe is fighting dragons while Hiccup sneaks out of the smithy with his bolas cannon
song.name: Dragon Battle

scene_description: Hiccup finds a Night Fury that he managed to down, but instead of killing he lets it go
song.name: The Downed Dragon

song.name: Dragon Training

scene_description: Hiccup notices that the Night Fury can't fly properly because of the missing part of the tail
song.name: Wounded
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: Hiccup reads the Dragon Book where all known to the tribe dragon species are listed
song.name: The Dragon Book
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: During the training session the youths try to find dragons' blind spots
song.name: Focus, Hiccup!
song.artist.name: John Powell

song.name: Forbidden Friendship

scene_description: Hiccup makes the missing part of the tail for Toothless
song.name: New Tail
song.artist.name: John Powell

song.name: See You Tomorrow
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: Toothless and Hiccup's first really successful flight
song.name: Test Drive
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: Hiccup realizes that everything that the Vikings know about dragons is wrong
song.name: Not So Fireproof
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: Hiccup wins the last round of the training without really intending to. Astrid is mad

scene_description: Toothless gives Astrid a hard ride until she gets so terrified that apologizes to Hiccup

scene_description: Toothless calms down at the same instant and gives them a really pleasant flight that completely charms Astrid

song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: Hiccup persuades Astrid to keep silence about the dragons' nest until he comes up with something
song.name: The Cove
song.artist.name: John Powell

scene_description: The youngsters appear at the battlefield, riding the dragons

scene_description: Hiccup is welcomed back as a hero
